### Problem19

Q: What is the difference between ++i and i++?
A: In expressions, both increment i, but ++i has the value _____(0)\___ (after/before) the increment and i++ have the value _____(1)\___ (after/before) the increment (from sec-1.3 Q&A)

Look at the code below:

```java
public class Test1
{
    public static void main(String[]args)
    {
        int i =1;
        int x =i++;
    }
}
```

```java
public class Test2
{
    public static void main(String[]args)
    {
        int i =1;
        int x =++i;
    }
}
```

The value of 'x' in Test1 is _____(2)\___, while the value of 'x' in Test2 is _____(3)\___.
